{"nodes": [{"id": "2026_06_05_prompt_range_algebra_kernel_design_document", "label": "Design", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-prompt-range-algebra-kernel/design.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_05_prompt_range_algebra_kernel_design_context", "label": "Context", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-prompt-range-algebra-kernel/design.md", "source_location": "line 1", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "`pi-vimmode` already has finite prompt-local editing semantics, but range handling is scattered: - `src/ex.ts` parses current Ex line addresses and destinations (`.`, `$`, numeric, `%`, `'<,'>`, comma ranges, destination `0`)."}, {"id": "2026_06_05_prompt_range_algebra_kernel_design_goals_non_goals", "label": "Goals / Non-Goals", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-prompt-range-algebra-kernel/design.md", "source_location": "line 12", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "**Goals:** - Introduce a pure prompt-local range algebra module for finite range parsing and resolution."}, {"id": "2026_06_05_prompt_range_algebra_kernel_design_decisions", "label": "Decisions", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-prompt-range-algebra-kernel/design.md", "source_location": "line 30", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "### Decision: Add a pure `src/range.ts` seam instead of expanding `src/ex.ts` or `src/buffer.ts` Target seams: `src/range.ts`, `src/ex.ts`, `src/buffer.ts`, `src/modal/engine.ts`."}, {"id": "2026_06_05_prompt_range_algebra_kernel_design_decision_add_a_pure_src_range_ts_seam_instead_of_expanding_src_ex_ts_or_src_buffer_ts", "label": "Decision: Add a pure src/range.ts seam instead of expanding src/ex.ts or src/buffer.ts", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-prompt-range-algebra-kernel/design.md", "source_location": "line 32", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `src/range.ts`, `src/ex.ts`, `src/buffer.ts`, `src/modal/engine.ts`. Create a pure module that exports typed parsers/resolvers for finite Ex prompt-local ranges plus typed wrappers for already-resolved line, character, block, and destination targets. `src/ex.ts` remains the finite command parser and delegates address/range parsing/resolution. `src/buffer.ts` remains the edit operation module and can consume typed resolved ranges through adapters. `src/modal/engine.ts` supplies Ex s"}, {"id": "2026_06_05_prompt_range_algebra_kernel_design_decision_model_range_parsing_as_finite_ast_plus_resolver_context", "label": "Decision: Model range parsing as finite AST plus resolver context", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-prompt-range-algebra-kernel/design.md", "source_location": "line 44", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `src/range.ts`, `src/ex.ts`, tests. Represent Ex address grammar as a small AST, then resolve with prompt context:"}, {"id": "2026_06_05_prompt_range_algebra_kernel_design_decision_define_semicolon_as_explicit_base_reset_not_broader_vim_expression_support", "label": "Decision: Define semicolon as explicit base reset, not broader Vim expression support", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-prompt-range-algebra-kernel/design.md", "source_location": "line 62", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `src/range.ts`, `src/ex.ts`, docs. For `addr1;addr2`, resolve `addr1`, then resolve `addr2` with current-line base set to `addr1`. This affects relative second addresses such as `;.+2`. It does not imply support for search-address commands, `+cmd`, expression evaluation, or repeated separators beyond the finite grammar documented in specs."}, {"id": "2026_06_05_prompt_range_algebra_kernel_design_decision_preserve_existing_side_effect_boundaries_resolver_returns_values_only", "label": "Decision: Preserve existing side-effect boundaries; resolver returns values only", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-prompt-range-algebra-kernel/design.md", "source_location": "line 73", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `src/modal/engine.ts`, `src/buffer.ts`, `src/vim-editor.ts`. Range resolution MUST NOT mutate prompt text, registers, marks, dot-repeat state, search state, visual state, Ex history, preview state, messages, or cursor. Modal/buffer operations remain responsible for side effects after successful resolution:"}, {"id": "2026_06_05_prompt_range_algebra_kernel_design_decision_migrate_incrementally_behind_compatibility_tests", "label": "Decision: Migrate incrementally behind compatibility tests", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-prompt-range-algebra-kernel/design.md", "source_location": "line 92", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: tests and implementation order. Start by covering existing behavior, then extract reusable parsing/resolution, then add offsets and semicolons. Existing tests for `:t0`, visual ranges, invalid ranges, substitution preview, delete/yank/put/copy/move/join, operator search/mark/motion, and visual operations must remain green."}, {"id": "2026_06_05_prompt_range_algebra_kernel_design_risks_trade_offs", "label": "Risks / Trade-offs", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-prompt-range-algebra-kernel/design.md", "source_location": "line 103", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "- Ex grammar sprawl \u2192 Mitigation: keep grammar finite, document non-goals, and reject unsupported syntax with readable Ex errors. - Semicolon semantics surprise users \u2192 Mitigation: specify base reset scenarios and document examples in `docs/features.md`. - Destination `0` regression \u2192 Mitigation: preserve `:2t0` and `:3,4m0` tests before changing destination parsing."}, {"id": "2026_06_05_prompt_range_algebra_kernel_design_migration_plan", "label": "Migration Plan", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-prompt-range-algebra-kernel/design.md", "source_location": "line 113", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "1. Add focused range parser/resolver tests for current Ex behavior, destination `0`, invalid ranges, offsets, and semicolon base semantics. 2. Add `src/range.ts` with AST, typed result/error shapes, and pure resolver context. 3. Refactor `src/ex.ts` to delegate Ex range and destination parsing/resolution while preserving current parse result shapes where callers depend on them."}, {"id": "2026_06_05_prompt_range_algebra_kernel_design_ref_src_ex_ts", "label": "ex.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-prompt-range-algebra-kernel/design.md", "source_location": "line 5", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_05_prompt_range_algebra_kernel_design_ref_src_buffer_ts", "label": "buffer.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-prompt-range-algebra-kernel/design.md", "source_location": "line 6", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_05_prompt_range_algebra_kernel_design_ref_src_modal_engine_ts", "label": "engine.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-prompt-range-algebra-kernel/design.md", "source_location": "line 7", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_05_prompt_range_algebra_kernel_design_ref_src_commands_ts", "label": "commands.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-prompt-range-algebra-kernel/design.md", "source_location": "line 8", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_05_prompt_range_algebra_kernel_design_ref_src_range_ts", "label": "range.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-prompt-range-algebra-kernel/design.md", "source_location": "line 32", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}], "edges": [{"source": "2026_06_05_prompt_range_algebra_kernel_design_document", "target": "2026_06_05_prompt_range_algebra_kernel_design_context", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-prompt-range-algebra-kernel/design.md", "source_location": "line 1", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "2026_06_05_prompt_range_algebra_kernel_design_document", "target": "2026_06_05_prompt_range_algebra_kernel_design_goals_non_goals", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-prompt-range-algebra-kernel/design.md", "source_location": "line 12", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "2026_06_05_prompt_range_algebra_kernel_design_document", "target": "2026_06_05_prompt_range_algebra_kernel_design_decisions", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-prompt-range-algebra-kernel/design.md", "source_location": "line 30", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "2026_06_05_prompt_range_algebra_kernel_design_document", "target": "2026